# Java Compilation Process

Source Code

```
Main.java
```

↓

Java Compiler

```
javac Main.java
```

↓

Bytecode

```
Main.class
```

↓

JVM

↓

Machine Code

↓

CPU

↓

Output

---

# Program Execution Flow

JVM Starts

↓

Finds `main()` Method

↓

Executes Statements

↓

Displays Output

↓

Program Ends

---

# Memory View (Current Stage)

During execution,

the `main()` method is placed on the call stack.

No objects are created yet,

so heap memory is not used.

---

# What is Time Complexity?

Time Complexity measures how the running time of an algorithm grows as the input size increases.

It measures the growth rate of an algorithm,

not the actual execution time in seconds.

Example

Input = 10

↓

10 Operations

Input = 100

↓

100 Operations

Growth

```
O(n)
```

We will study Big O Notation in detail later.

